76.description:
Justin Timberlake’s Family ‘Couldn’t Ask for a Better Daughter-In-Law,’ Says Aunt (EXCLUSIVE): 
Jessica Biel may...  Jessica Biel may be saying “I do” to Justin Timberlake this weekend — but she’s already got his family’s approval. “We couldn’t ask for a better daughter-in-law,” the pop star’s aunt Jane Harless gushed to Celebuzz. “We just love her.” Harless, who was invited to the Italian nuptials, said she had to skip the 6,000-mile trip to care for the star's grandparents, William and Sadie Bomar, in Tennessee.  “They’re both disabled so I’m staying with them and helping them,” she said, adding she they all wished they could be there to see Timberlake walk down the aisle. “It’s heartbreaking." Still, their hearts are with the happy couple. “I wish them the best and I know they’re going to be very happy,” Jane said. Meanwhile, Timberlake's cousin, Heather Bomar, said her mother, Kathy, was able to make the trip to Southern Italy. "The last I heard she was in Germany and then caught a plane,” she said. Justin Timberlake and Jessica Biel were married Friday, the couple...  Justin Timberlake and Jessica Biel were married Friday, the couple has confirmed. "It's great to be married, the ceremony was beautiful and it was so special to be surrounded by our family and friends," they said in a joint statement. The news follows a full week of speculation about the top-secret nuptials, which took place in front of approximately 80 loved ones at the church on the grounds of the Borgo Engazia resort in Puglia, Italy, Celebuzz has confirmed. The celebrations began earlier this week, with an evening bash at the beachfront resort of Riva Dei Ginepri. During the soiree, partygoers — which included guests like Saturday Night Live alum Andy Samberg and Biel's former 7th Heaven co-star, Beverly Mitchell — soon took in the majestic Southern Italy scenery, traditional Neapolitan music and a dazzling 10-minute fireworks display.
